===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Inconclusive.
* Jì Xùshēng: {{liushu|ls=ic}} a mouth {{zh-l|*口}} giving orders and a scepter {{zh-l|*刁}} of authority. 
* Liú Xìnglóng interprets {{zh-l|*刁}} to be a hand instead. 
* Táng Lán: Originally the same character as {{zh-l|*后}}, which later diverged.
* ''{{w|Shuowen}}'': {{zh-l|*后}} flipped.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*zə}}; cognate with Proto-Kukish {{m|und|*ca}}, {{cog|mro|caŋ||to do; to make}}, and {{cog|bo|མཛད||to do; to act}}, {{m|bo|མཛོད}}, possibly also related to {{m|bo|བཟོ|t=work, labour}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Schuessler disputes {{zh-ref|Löffler's (1966)}} proposed connection of these cognates to {{och-l|作|to do, work, make}} due to phonological difficulties.

{{zh-ref|Unger (1984)}} posits a possible relationship with {{cog|bo|རྫི་པོ|t=herdsman}}.

